arcade.patch.agent.cell

Class PatchCellFactory

  • java.lang.Object
    • arcade.patch.agent.cell.PatchCellFactory
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    CellFactory

    public final class PatchCellFactory
extends java.lang.Object
implements CellFactory
    Implementation of CellFactory for PatchCell agents.

    For a given Series, the factory parses out parameter values into a series of maps from population to the parameter values. These maps are then combined with a PatchCellContainer to instantiate a PatchCell agent.

    Cell volumes (CELL_VOLUME_MEAN, CELL_VOLUME_STDEV) and cell heights (CELL_HEIGHT_MEAN, CELL_HEIGHT_STDEV) are drawn from normal distributions. Cell ages (CELL_AGE_MIN, CELL_AGE_MAX) are drawn from a uniform distribution. Cell division potential is initialized to DIVISION_POTENTIAL. Cell compression tolerance (COMPRESSION_TOLERANCE) is added to the cell critical height.

        public void loadCells(Series series)
        Loads cell containers into the factory container.

        Population sizes are determined from the given series. The list of loaded containers is filtered by population code and population size so that extra containers are discarded.

        Specified by:

      • parseValues

        void parseValues(Series series)
        Parses the population settings into maps to parameter value.

        Loaded parameters include:

        • CELL_VOLUME_MEAN = cell volume distribution average
        • CELL_VOLUME_STDEV = cell volume distribution standard deviation
        • CELL_HEIGHT_MEAN = cell height distribution average
        • CELL_HEIGHT_STDEV = cell height distribution standard deviation
        • CELL_AGE_MIN = minimum cell age
        • CELL_AGE_MAX = maximum cell age
        • DIVISION_POTENTIAL = maximum number of divisions
        • COMPRESSION_TOLERANCE = maximum compression tolerance
        Parameters:
        series - the simulation series
